or to April 25, 2022, the Fund did not invest directly in portfolio securities and did not require investment advisory services.\n\nAll portfolio management occurred at the Master Portfolio level.\n\nThe Master LLC, on behalf of the Master Portfolio, was party to a management agreement with the Manager pursuant to which the Manager provided the Master LLC with investment advisory and management services with respect to the Master Portfolio.\n\nEffective April 25, 2022, the Corporation, on behalf of the Fund, entered into the Management Agreement with substantially identical terms, conditions and fees as those of the management agreement between BlackRock and the Master LLC, on behalf of the Master Portfolio.\n\nThe information shown below for periods prior to April 25, 2022 reflects the “master/feeder” structure in place prior to April 25, 2022.\n\nBlackRock has contractually agreed to waive the management fee with respect to any portion of the Fund’s assets estimated to be attributable to investments in other equity and fixed-income mutual funds and exchange-traded funds managed by BlackRock or its affiliates that have a contractual management fee, through June 30, 2026.','\n',char(10)));
