viders.  The Trust reimburses all Trustees and officers for travel and other expenses related to meetings.  Compensation figures reflect the Fund''s fiscal year ended November 30, 2023.  There is mention of an additional $3,300 expected to be paid to each trustee for a different series of the Trust in the upcoming fiscal year.  Ronald F. Rohe passed away in November 2023, and Bradley J. Alden resigned in January 2024."\n}\n','\n',char(10)),replace('=== chunk 64 === \nReferences to the qualifications, attributes and skills of Trustees are pursuant to requirements of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (the “SEC”), do not constitute holding out the Board or any Trustee as having any special expertise or experience, and shall not impose any greater responsibility on any such person or on the Board by reason thereof.\n\nTrustee Standing Committees.\n\nThe Trustees have established the following standing committees:\n\nAudit Committee: All of the Independent Trustees are members of the Audit Committee, with Mr. Rogan serving as the Audit Committee Chair and financial expert.\n\nThe Audit Committee oversees the Fund’s accounting and financial reporting policies and practices, reviews the results of the annual audits of the Fund’s financial statements, and interacts with the Fund’s independent auditors on behalf of all the Trustees.\n\nThe Audit Committee also serves as the Trust’s qualified legal compliance committee.\n\nThe Audit\n\n24  \n---  \n  \n---  \n  \nCommittee operates pursuant to an Audit Committee Charter and meets periodically as necessary.\n\nThe Audit Committee met 2 times during the Fund’s last fiscal year.\n\nNominating Committee: All of the Independent Trustees are members of the Nominating Committee.\n\nThe Nominating Committee nominates, selects and appoints independent trustees to fill vacancies on the Board and to stand for election at meeting of the shareholders of the Trust.\n\nThe Nominating Committee generally will not consider nominees recommended by shareholders of the Trust.\n\nThe Nominating Committee meets only as necessary and it did not meet during the Fund’s last fiscal year.\n\nProxy Voting Committee: All of the Independent Trustees are members of the Proxy Voting Committee.\n\nThe Proxy Voting Committee will determine how the Fund should cast its vote, if called upon by the Board or the Advisor, when a matter with respect to which the Fund is entitled to vote presents a conflict between the interests of the Fund’s shareholders, on the one hand, and those of the Fund’s Advisor, principal underwriter or an affiliated person of the Fund, its investment adviser, or principal underwriter, on the other hand.\n\nThe Proxy Voting Committee will also review the Trust’s Proxy Voting Policy and recommend any changes to the Board as it deems necessary or advisable.\n\nThe Proxy Voting Committee meets only as necessary and did not meet during the Fund’s last fiscal year.\n\n25  \n---  \n  \n---  \n  \nBeneficial Equity Ownership Information.\n\nThe table below shows for each Trustee the amount of Fund equity securities beneficially owned by each Trustee and the aggregate value of all investments in equity securities of the Fund complex, as of a valuation date of December 31, 2023 and stated as one of the following ranges: A = None; B = $1-$10,000; C = 10,001-$50,000; D - $50,001-100,000; and E = over $100,000.\n\nName of Director |  Fund |  Dollar Range of Equity Securities in a Fund | Aggregate Dollar Range of Equity Securities in All Registered Investment Companies Overseen by Director in Family of Investment Companies  \n---|---|---|---  \nIndependent Trustees  \nDonald H. Baxter | Large Cap Fund | A | A  \n|  |  |   \nMichael G. Rogan | Large Cap Fund | A | A  \nInterested Trustees  \nCharles S. Stoll | Large Cap Fund | E | E  \n  \nAs of December 31, 2023, the officers and Trustees of the Trust, in the aggregate, owned of record or beneficially more than 1% of the outstanding shares of the Large Cap Fund.\n=== chunk 65 === \nOwnership of Securities of Advisor, Distributor or Related Entities.\n\nAs of December 31, 2023, none of the Independent Trustees and/or their immediate family members owned securities of the Advisor, Arbor Court Capital, LLC or any entity controlling, controlled by, or under common control with the Advisor or the Distributor.\n\n26  \n---  \n  \n---  \n  \nCompensation.\n\nOfficers of the Trust and Trustees who are “interested persons” of the Trust or the Advisor will receive no salary or fees from the Trust.\n\nOfficers of the Trust and interested Trustees do receive compensation directly from certain service providers to the Trust, including Arbor Court Capital, LLC, Premier Fund Solutions, Inc. and Mutual Shareholder Services, LLC.\n\nEach Trustee who is not an “interested person” receives a fee of $2,500 each year plus $200 per Board or committee meeting attended.\n\nThe Trust reimburses each Trustee and officer for his or her travel and other expenses relating to attendance at such meetings.\n\nTrustee compensation for the Fund’s fiscal year ended November 30, 2023 was as follows:\n\nName of Trustee |  Aggregate Compensation Paid for Service by the Fund |  Pension or Retirement Benefits Accrued As Part of Fund Expenses |  |  Estimated Annual Benefits Upon Retirement |  Total Compensation From Fund Complex Paid to Trustees*  \n---|---|---|---|---|---  \nIndependent Trustees  \nDonald H. Baxter | $3,300 |\n\nN/A |  | N/A | $6,600  \nRonald F. Rohe** | $3,300 | N/A |  | N/A | $6,600  \nMichael G. Rogan | $3,300 | N/A |  | N/A | $6,600  \nInterested Trustees  \nCharles S. Stoll |\n\nNone | N/A |  |\n\nN/A | None  \nBradley J. Alden*** |\n\nNone | N/A |  |\n\nN/A | None  \n  \n*\n\nEach of the Trustees serves as a Trustee to each series of the Trust.\n\nThe Trust currently offers two (2) series of shares.\n\nOne series of the Trust is in a separate SAI.\n\nThat series has a different fiscal year end, and like the fund included in this SAI, is expected to pay the Trustees each $3,300 for this upcoming fiscal year.\n\n** Mr. Rohe served as an Independent Trustee until his death in November 2023.\n\n*** Mr. Alden served as an Interested Trustee until his resignation as a Trustee in January 2024.\n\nPrincipal Holders of Fund Shares\n\nAs of March 6, 2024, the following persons owned of record 5% or more of the outstanding shares of the Fund:\n\nCharles Schwab & Co., Inc.\n\nFor Benefit of Customers 211 Main Street San Francisco, California 94105 | 1,650,968.63 | 99.99% | Record  \n---|---|---|---  \n  \n27  \n---  \n  \n---  \n  \nMANAGEMENT AND ADMINISTRATION\n\nInvestment Adviser.\n\nWinning Points Advisors, LLC serves as the investment adviser to the Fund.\n\nThe Advisor’s principal office is located at 127 NW 13th Street, Suite 13, Boca Raton, Florida 33432.\n\nInformation about the Advisor and its duties and compensation as Advisor is contained in the Prospectus.\n\nThe Advisor is a Florida limited liability company and registered as an investment adviser under the Investment Advisers Act of 1940, as amended.\n\nThe Advisor supervises the Fund’s investments pursuant to an investment advisory agreement with the Trust.\n\nThe Advisory Agreement is effective for an initial two-year period and will be renewed thereafter only so long as such renewal and continuance is specifically approved at least annually by the Trustees or by vote of a majority of each Fund’s outstanding voting securities, provided the continuance is also approved by a majority of the Trustees who are not parties to the Advisory Agreement or interested persons of any such party.','\n',char(10)));
